Round 1: 
[Patient] "How much water should I drink every day?"
[Healthcare Educator] "Try to drink around 8 cups of water each day."
 
Round 2:
[Patient] "Can I drink other fluids like juice or tea?"
[Healthcare Educator] "Yes, but try to limit sugary drinks and caffeine."

Round 3:
[Patient] "Is there a specific time I should drink water?"
[Healthcare Educator] "It's good to spread out your water intake throughout the day."

Round 4:
[Patient] "What if I feel thirsty all the time?"
[Healthcare Educator] "Drink water when you're thirsty, but don't force yourself to drink too much."

Round 5:
[Patient] "How can I remember to drink enough water?"
[Healthcare Educator] "Try setting reminders on your phone or keeping a water bottle with you."